<div id="review_3492350558" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3492350558" />
    <a title="P. E." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40350320-p-e"><img alt="P. E." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1424130572p2/40350320.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3492350558?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="P. E." class="user" itemprop="url" name="P. E." href="/user/show/40350320-p-e">P. E.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3492350558" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17168306822833442878">This is the fourth book I&apos;ve read by Mario Puzo, and I am really enjoying his writing style and storytelling ability. Initially I had a little trouble getting into the book, but that only intensified my determination to dive in and read. The book is broken up in four sections of backstory, all crucial to the plot. It was the individual parts that I really enjoyed, each section pulling back the veil of actions leading up to the climax. The book&apos;s ending surprised me, but that is the mastery of Pu</span>
  <span id="freeText17168306822833442878" style="display:none">This is the fourth book I've read by Mario Puzo, and I am really enjoying his writing style and storytelling ability. Initially I had a little trouble getting into the book, but that only intensified my determination to dive in and read. The book is broken up in four sections of backstory, all crucial to the plot. It was the individual parts that I really enjoyed, each section pulling back the veil of actions leading up to the climax. The book's ending surprised me, but that is the mastery of Puzo working his craft.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17168306822833442878" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
