<div id="review_1446311624" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1446311624" />
    <a title="Vikalp Trivedi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39776026-vikalp-trivedi"><img alt="Vikalp Trivedi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433140916p2/39776026.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1446311624?book_show_action=true">Nov 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vikalp Trivedi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vikalp Trivedi" href="/user/show/39776026-vikalp-trivedi">Vikalp Trivedi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39776026-vikalp-trivedi?shelf=reading-challenge-2016">reading-challenge-2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1446311624" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7902591273476766993">&apos;The Sicilian&apos; is the sequel to the cult classic &apos;The Godfather&apos; and chronicles the times of Michael Corleone&apos;s exile in Sicily . The novel is based on the real life exploits of Salvatore &quot;Turi&quot; Giuliano (spelling was intentionally changed in the novel ) . <br/><br/>The best things I found about this book is that the situations of transformation of &quot;lad Turi&quot; to &quot;bandit Turi&quot; are still relevant . There are numerous stories throughout our nation same as Turi&apos;s . The second best thing about the book is its </span>
  <span id="freeText7902591273476766993" style="display:none">'The Sicilian' is the sequel to the cult classic 'The Godfather' and chronicles the times of Michael Corleone's exile in Sicily . The novel is based on the real life exploits of Salvatore "Turi" Giuliano (spelling was intentionally changed in the novel ) . <br /><br />The best things I found about this book is that the situations of transformation of "lad Turi" to "bandit Turi" are still relevant . There are numerous stories throughout our nation same as Turi's . The second best thing about the book is its character building . Each and every character is used very intelligently by the author . <br /><br />The plot of the book lacked the enigma which its prequel had . The book was more biographical then fiction . In many places the situations are stratched by uselessly describing the personality of the protagonist and it is repeated again and again throughout the novel . The plot is plain with completely predictable twists . The dialogues were nowhere near the great dialogues of the prequel . <br /><br />Overall a good read . Not as great as "The Godfather" .<br /><br />3.5 Stars .</span>
  <a data-text-id="7902591273476766993" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


