<div id="review_3503920320" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3503920320" />
    <a title="Dwarakeshwaran Malathi Magesh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25937504-dwarakeshwaran-malathi-magesh"><img alt="Dwarakeshwaran Malathi Magesh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1587250401p2/25937504.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3503920320?book_show_action=true">Dec 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dwarakeshwaran Malathi Magesh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dwarakeshwaran Malathi Magesh" href="/user/show/25937504-dwarakeshwaran-malathi-magesh">Dwarakeshwaran Malathi Magesh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099414742" href="/book/show/826446.The_Sicilian">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3503920320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17740796726688862461">This book felt like an unnecessary filler for its predecessor novel. But its...<br/><br/><b>NOT!!!!</b><br/><br/>The climax of this book was awesome which defined the character of Corleone guys.<br/><br/>The &quot;Politics&quot; part of this book was fictionalized in a more comprehending way. The contradiction of the Democratic Party and the Socialist (or Communist?) Party and its intricacies were defined through the character of the Protoganist and the Antagonist.<br/><br/>This 400-Page filler of The Godfather is a must-read, not only for the politic</span>
  <span id="freeText17740796726688862461" style="display:none">This book felt like an unnecessary filler for its predecessor novel. But its...<br /><br /><b>NOT!!!!</b><br /><br />The climax of this book was awesome which defined the character of Corleone guys.<br /><br />The "Politics" part of this book was fictionalized in a more comprehending way. The contradiction of the Democratic Party and the Socialist (or Communist?) Party and its intricacies were defined through the character of the Protoganist and the Antagonist.<br /><br />This 400-Page filler of The Godfather is a must-read, not only for the political story of this book but also, to know why Michael Corleone had changed from a man to The Don! (Sort of...)<br /><br /><blockquote>நாம வாழணும்னா யார வேணாலும் எத்தன பேர வேணாலும் கொல்லலாம்! <br /> - <s>Thala Ajith Kumar</s> Don Corleone :D </blockquote><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17740796726688862461" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


